    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "This E92 M3 is a mechanically sorted example featuring the legendary S65B40 naturally aspirated V8. The engine exhibits a linear power band peaking at an 8,400 RPM redline, with the individual throttle bodies providing instantaneous transient response. Significant preventative maintenance has been addressed, including the replacement of rod bearings and throttle actuators, ensuring the longevity of the high-revving rotating assembly. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a 6-speed manual transmission and an M-Variable limited-slip differential, providing superior corner-exit traction. The chassis retains its composure with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and remains free of subframe fatigue. While the aesthetic condition shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical synchronization and hydraulic steering feedback remain sharp and uncompromised.",
